                    <p>Without quill ricochet (from Needleflare Gauntlets or the Aspect), each Quill Volley only hits enemies in the cone. With ricochet, quills bounce between all nearby enemies, turning every pack into a chain reaction of poison.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Attack speed is your most important stat.</strong>
                    <p>More Quill Volleys per second means more poison stacks, more ricochet hits, and exponentially more damage through Noxious Resonance scaling. Prioritize attack speed on every gear slot possible.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Let poison finish the job.</strong>
                    <p>You don't need to kill enemies with direct quill hits. Apply heavy poison stacks and move to the next pack. The DoT will finish off weakened enemies while you're already clearing ahead.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Stay at mid-range for safety.</strong>
                    <p>Quill Volley has excellent range. There is no reason to be in melee. Keep your distance and let the quills do the work. Use Soar and Evade to maintain safe positioning at all times.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Ring of Starless Skies solves Vigor issues.</strong>
                    <p>Without this mythic ring, Quill Volley spam drains Vigor quickly. With it, each consecutive cast reduces cost until you're casting for nearly free. This is the single biggest quality-of-life upgrade for the build.</p>
